        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 6:37PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Scattered snow showers will move southward down the front range of
the Rocky Mountain Front early this evening.

Some of the snow showers could reduce visibility below a half mile
at times, with snow accumulations up to an inch on grassy areas.

Some minor snow accumulations are also possible on bridges.

Those traveling in areas around Dupuyer, Choteau, Fairfield, Craig
and over MacDonald Pass should be prepared for quickly changing
road conditions and areas of poor visibility.
</description>
